reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful and organic looking
reviews.reviewText: I am very happy with this set of kitchen utensils from WRPLU. They are not only beautiful and organic looking, but also very functional and durable. The wood in the middle of the handles is smooth and comfortable to hold, and the silicone tips are gentle on my non-stick pans. The set comes with everything I need for cooking, baking, and serving, including a utensil holder and hooks for hanging. They look great on my kitchen counter and add a touch of elegance to my decor. I think this is a perfect Valentine’s gift for anyone who loves to cook. I highly recommend this product to anyone looking for quality and style in their kitchen utensils.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Unfortunately the set is not FULL silicone which was the entire point of buying it. The measuring cups, and both potato mashers are plastic. The wood handles have some knicks in them. Just cheap. Buy a more expensive kit if you appreciate nice things.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Just not impressed
reviews.reviewText: I don't have much good to share about these. The handles are wood, the dishwasher would ruin them, and the utensils themselves are too small for my liking; they don't make the job of cooking easy, and they're just not made with quality materials.They might make a good starter set for a young person starting out, but I might be embarrassed to even give them as a gift. Sadly, I can't recommend them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent utensil set
reviews.reviewText: Everything seems to be of pretty good quality. It'll be nice finally having a matching set of various cooking utensils instead of all the randoms I've built up over the years. Pictures are accurate, including the 10 S-Hooks and container. Subtract 11 pieces from the full count and you end up with 22 actual utensils. Still breaks down to just over a buck a piece, so that's good in my book.Should be noted though that whatever finish they use on the wood isn't good. It was about 50% gone after the first run through the dishwasher and completely gone after the second run.I am going refinish/seal them with linseed oil and they should be fine.I would recommend gently hand washing and drying immediately if you don't have a way to properly seal them after washing the original finish off.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This set was is so cute and I love the color and the wood. Now the only 1 I was not a fan of was the potato smasher it really didn't smash much but other then that this set is nice and would recommend this is a gift.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a great set with everything you need. It also has the matching holder. They are sturdy and easy to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I recently ordered this set of kitchen utensils and overall, I think they work fine. However, I do have one major issue with them - they are really small. This has caused quite a problem for me in the kitchen as they don't quite do the job they are intended for. I wish they were a bit larger to make them more practical for everyday use. Overall, I think they are okay, but the size is a big drawback.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great selection!! Has just about everything you need for a starter kitchen. Not crazy about the wooden handles. The utensil chart is labeled wrong, I had to tell my son what each one was.
